.:: Einstein-puzzle ::.

The people use 5 different means of transport: trike, train, skateboard, car, bus
5 different games are played: mah-jongg, backgammon, go, scrabble, monopoly
City: marseilles, rome, venice, paris, miami
House: trikemaster, tower, wooden, ranch-style, art-deco
5 different pets are kept: cat, bird, dog, fish, horse
1. the person playing mah-jongg is the person driving the skateboard
2. the person playing swedish is the owner of the dog
3. the person playing backgammon is the person traveling to paris
4. the person driving the train is on the left of the person driving the car
5. the person driving the train is the person traveling to rome
6. the wooden house is the owner of the bird
7. the person driving the bus is the tower house
8. the person traveling to venice is in the middle
9. the person playing scrabble is on the far left
10. the art-deco house is on the left or right of the owner of the cat
11. the owner of the horses is on the left or right of the tower house
12. the trikemaster house is the person traveling to marseilles
13. the person playing go is the ranch-style house
14. the person playing scrabble is on the left or right of the person driving the trike
15. the art-deco house is on the left or right of the person traveling to miami

.:: Answer ::.
|		|	1	|	2	|	3	|	4	|	5	|
| Transport		|    bus	|     trike	|      skateboard	|     train	|     car	|
| Game	|   scrabble	|    backgammon	|    mah-jongg	|    go	|    swedish	|
| Pet		|     cat	|    horse	|     bird	|     fish	|      dog	|
| City	|    miami	|     paris	|     venice	|    rome	|      marseilles	|
| House		|   tower	|    art-deco	|  wooden	|    ranch-style	|   trikemaster	|
